## This is the Dockerfile for the router

```Dockerfile
FROM quay.io/frrouting/frr:10.6.0

RUN apk update

RUN sed -i 's/^bgpd=no/bgpd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons \
    && sed -i 's/^ospfd=no/ospfd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons \
    && sed -i 's/^isisd=no/isisd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons
```


## Build the image

Go to the directory containing the Dockerfile and run the following command:

```bash
docker build . -t router_arazafin:p1
```

or run this command from anywhere:

```bash
docker build -t router_arazafin:p1 - <<EOF
FROM quay.io/frrouting/frr:10.6.0
RUN apk update
RUN sed -i 's/^bgpd=no/bgpd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons \
    && sed -i 's/^ospfd=no/ospfd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons \
    && sed -i 's/^isisd=no/isisd=yes/' /etc/frr/daemons
EOF
```
